fields.name: Mountain Tea
fields.description: Mountain Tea is green tea grown on the side of Yellow Mountain. It has a tart taste with many health benefits, such is decreasing blood pressure and aiding digestion.

fields.name: Pink Tea
fields.description: Pink tea is a rosy-hued variety of tea that is the luxurious, special-occasion drink of choice for Pakistanis. Pink tea is a creamy, milky citrus. Like a Creamsicle with flowers in it.

fields.name: Daisy Tea
fields.description: Daisy tea is a flower tea with a fragrant smell as well as taste. It has particularly beneficial for those with throat problems and who use their voice for work.

fields.name: Green Tea
fields.description: Our Green Tea is also known as Dragon Well Tea. This tea is considered the Lamborghini of Teas. Dragon Well Tea tastes like spring's first green vegetables accented by roasted chestnut. Green tea has been shown to improve blood flow and lower cholesterol.

fields.name: Peach Tea
fields.description: An adult iced tea that mixes vodka and peach tea. Health benefits? It might help you to relax but don't forget to drink in moderation.

fields.name: Taiwanese Bubble Tea
fields.description: The whimsy that is milky tea with delicious tapioca balls will. transport you to a food tour in Taiwan.

fields.name: Tea Tasting
fields.description: Come visit us at our Chapel Street location in Cork City where we will guide you through teas from Sri Lanka, China and India.

fields.name: Bubble Tea Making
fields.description: Come visit us at our Chapel Street location in Cork City where we will guide you how to make a selection of Bubble Teas.
